body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to XYZ Car Dealership customer support. My name is Daniel Garcia.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: May I please know your name so I can assist you better?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Natalie. How may I assist you today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I am feeling nervous about the returns process.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand your concern, Natalie. To assist you, could you please provide me with the last four digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it is seven five six two.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Natalie. Additionally, may I please confirm the first three digits of your postal code?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, it is M two X.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Natalie. Your concerns are noted. Is there anything else I can do for you today?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Natalie. Please feel free to contact us if you need further assistance. Have a great day!
